<p><a name="Peripatetic_nomads" id="Peripatetic_nomads"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Nomad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Peripatetic nomads">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Peripatetic nomads</span></h2>
<div class="rellink">Further information: <a href="/wiki/Nomadic_peoples_of_Europe" title="Nomadic peoples of Europe">Nomadic peoples of Europe</a></div>
<p>"Peripatetic nomads" are mobile populations moving among settled populations offering a <a href="/wiki/Craft" title="Craft">craft</a> or <a href="/wiki/Trade" title="Trade">trade</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Romani_people" title="Romani people">Roma</a> (Gypsies)
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Kalderash" title="Kalderash">Kalderash</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Gitano" title="Gitano" class="mw-redirect">Gitano</a> (AKA <a href="/wiki/Cale" title="Cale">Cale</a>)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Manush" title="Manush">Manush</a> (AKA <a href="/wiki/Sinti" title="Sinti">Sinti</a>)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Romnichal" title="Romnichal" class="mw-redirect">Romnichal</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Irish_Travellers" title="Irish Travellers" class="mw-redirect">Irish Travellers</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yeniche_people" title="Yeniche people">Yeniche</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Quinqui" title="Quinqui">Quinqui</a></li>
</ul>
